Iavan Pijoos, News24 Johannesburg – The second leg of the inquiry into the collapse of the Grayston Drive pedestrian bridge, which killed two people, will begin on May 6. The first session allowed those involved in the project – construction company, Murray & Roberts; scaffolding supplier, Form Scaff, and engineering consultancy firm, Royal HaskoningDHV – to outline their involvement in the project. A driver of a minibus taxi and a man in a Toyota Fortuner were killed. The bridge over the M1 at Grayston Drive collapsed on October 14 last year.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  